td.p:
Regulation (EC) No 178/2002 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 28 January 2002 laying down the general principles and requirements of food law, establishing the European Food Safety Authority and laying down procedures in matters of food safety (
OJ 2002 L 31, p. 1
), as amended by Regulation No 652/2014 (‘Regulation No 178/2002’), provides the basis for ensuring a high level of protection of human health and consumers’ interest in relation to food, taking into account in particular the diversity in the supply of food.
